# motoquencer "I Feel Lucky": luckygateprob with luckyamount=1 is the deterministic
# extreme -- it sets every affected step's gate-probability to the maximum 7 ("7 =
# always"), i.e. it disables randomization so the gates always play. We observe the
# result through the motor-fader readback: with fadermode=2 the faders show the
# gate-probability lane (position = gateprob/7). We first pull all four to 0, then a
# luckygateprob trigger snaps them (and the motors) to the top, position 1.0.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[m4]
[motoquencer]
    numfaders     = 4
    fadermode     = 2
    clock         = I1
    luckygateprob = I2
>>>
# tick1: dial the gate-probability lane down to 0 on every fader.
@1 move F1 0.0
@1 move F2 0.0
@1 move F3 0.0
@1 move F4 0.0
@1 expect F1 0.0 tol 1e-4
@1 expect F2 0.0 tol 1e-4
# tick2: fire luckygateprob (luckyamount defaults to 1) -> gateprob = 7 for every
# affected step; the lucky reroll re-commands the motors to the top notch (1.0).
@2 set I2 1
@2 expect F1 1.0 tol 1e-4
@2 expect F2 1.0 tol 1e-4
@2 expect F3 1.0 tol 1e-4
@2 expect F4 1.0 tol 1e-4
